{
  "name": "smart-apartment-backend",
  "dockerComposeFile": ["../../docker-compose.yml"],
  "service": "backend",
  "workspaceFolder": "/app",
  "runServices": ["db", "backend"],
  "forwardPorts": [8000, 5432],
  "customizations": {
    "vscode": {
      "extensions": ["ms-python.python", "ms-python.vscode-pylance"]
    }
  },
  "postCreateCommand": "python -m pip install -r requirements.txt || true"
}

/*Otwieranie projektu

Otwórz w VS Code folder backend/

Ctrl+Shift+P → Dev Containers: Reopen in Container

Po tym:

terminal w VS Code jest “z kontenera”

Pylance widzi importy z kontenera (Django itd.)

python manage.py ... działa bez instalowania czegokolwiek lokalnie (u Was manage.py odpala projekt config.settings). 

manage
*/